# Production Readiness — A2Z Tools ERP

**Audience:** CTO, DevOps, release managers  
**Last updated:** June 2026  
**Related:** [PRODUCTION_DEPLOYMENT_PLAN.md](./PRODUCTION_DEPLOYMENT_PLAN.md) · [DEPLOYMENT_ARCHITECTURE.md](./DEPLOYMENT_ARCHITECTURE.md) · [deployment.md](./deployment.md)

---

## Infrastructure Architecture

Production runs as **Docker Compose on a Sydney-region origin host** with **Cloudflare** at the edge. Only Nginx exposes ports 80/443; PostgreSQL and Redis are internal.

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Edge[Cloudflare]
        DNS[DNS + WAF + DDoS]
        CDN[CDN — storefront static]
    end

    subgraph Origin[Origin host — /opt/a2z-tools]
        NGX[Nginx :443]
        FE[frontend :3000]
        BE[backend Gunicorn :8000]
        CW[celery + beat]
        PG[(PostgreSQL 16)]
        RD[(Redis 7)]
    end

    subgraph Offsite[Offsite services]
        GHCR[GHCR container images]
        S3[(S3 / R2 backups)]
        SNT[Sentry]
        UPT[Uptime monitoring]
    end

    Users[Customers + Staff] --> DNS
    DNS --> CDN
    CDN -->|www| NGX
    DNS -->|dashboard + api| NGX
    NGX --> FE
    NGX --> BE
    BE --> PG
    BE --> RD
    CW --> PG
    CW --> RD
    BE --> SNT
    PG -->|pg_dump daily| S3
    RD -->|RDB daily| S3
    BE -->|media weekly| S3
    GHCR --> Origin
    UPT --> DNS
```

### Component map

| Layer | Technology | Config / scripts |
|-------|------------|------------------|
| Edge | Cloudflare DNS, WAF, cache | `infrastructure/cloudflare/` |
| Reverse proxy | Nginx 1.27 | `infrastructure/nginx/` |
| API | Django 5 + Gunicorn | `backend/Dockerfile`, `config/settings/prod.py` |
| Storefront + Admin UI | Next.js 15 standalone | `frontend/Dockerfile` |
| Workers | Celery + Redis broker | `docker-compose.prod.yml --profile workers` |
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 | Internal Docker network |
| Cache / queue | Redis 7 | Internal Docker network |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions → GHCR → SSH | `.github/workflows/` |
| Secrets | GitHub Environments, host `.env` | `.env.production.example` |
| Backups | pg_dump, Redis RDB, media tar → S3 | `infrastructure/scripts/backup-*.sh` |
| Monitoring | Sentry, JSON logs, external probes | `config/sentry.py`, `healthchecks.example.yaml` |

### Health endpoints

| Probe | URL | Purpose |
|-------|-----|---------|
| API liveness | `GET /api/v1/health/` | Process alive |
| API readiness | `GET /api/v1/ready/` | Postgres + Redis |
| Frontend | `GET /api/health` | Next.js alive |
| Nginx internal | `GET :8080/health` | Proxy alive |

---

## Production Readiness Score

**Overall: 78 / 100 — Ready for controlled go-live with documented gaps**

| Area | Score | Status | Notes |
|------|-------|--------|-------|
| Containerization | 92 | ✅ Strong | Multi-stage Dockerfiles, prod compose, non-root users |
| Environment & secrets | 85 | ✅ Good | Templates + `validate-production-env.sh`; secrets external |
| Health checks | 88 | ✅ Good | DB + Redis readiness; frontend `/api/health` |
| CI (test gate) | 85 | ✅ Good | Backend + frontend CI on main/develop |
| CD (deploy pipeline) | 75 | ⚠️ Adequate | GHCR + Trivy + SSH; prod CI gate advisory |
| Observability | 70 | ⚠️ Adequate | Sentry wired; no Prometheus/Grafana yet |
| Backups | 80 | ✅ Good | Scripts + cron template; weekly verify drill |
| Disaster recovery | 72 | ⚠️ Adequate | Restore scripts; manual DR test required |
| Security scanning | 78 | ✅ Good | Trivy, pip-audit, npm audit, Gitleaks, Dependabot |
| Load testing | 65 | ⚠️ Baseline | k6 scripts provided; run before peak traffic |
| Documentation | 90 | ✅ Strong | Runbooks, architecture, this readiness doc |
| RBAC & audit | 88 | ✅ Strong | Enterprise RBAC; `OperationalAuditLog` |

**Go-live recommendation:** Proceed to **staging soak** → **production cutover** after completing the Go-Live Checklist below and achieving load-test thresholds on staging.

---

## Risk Assessment

| ID | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation | Owner |
|----|------|------------|--------|------------|-------|
| R1 | Database loss without restore | Low | Critical | Nightly pg_dump to S3; weekly `verify-backup-restore.sh` | DevOps |
| R2 | Secret leak in repo or logs | Medium | Critical | Gitleaks CI; never commit `.env`; rotate on exposure | Security |
| R3 | Deploy without passing CI | Medium | High | Branch protection on `main`; prod deploy manual only | Eng lead |
| R4 | Redis/Celery outage outage outage

StrReplace